history.content: Just my two cents but I doubt you'll be able to get into 188 in the fall if you haven't signed up already. It looks to be almost full in both direct enrollment and waitlist, so you would be well off the 10% rule. If your goal is just to get into ANY CS upper div, I'd look at 186 or 161, as those are usually the ones that are still possible to get into this late in the game.

children.subject: I can't take 161 because I haven't taken 61C :( 186 doesn't sound particularly appealing to me but maybe I'll just keep it as a backup. Thanks!

history.content: Please note that if you're applying over the summer, the application is due Aug 15. It will take approx. two weeks for your summer grades to become official, and then 2-3 weeks for us to review and process all the applications. You would not be declared until sometime in September

Hi,

If things work out like I hope, I will be declared by the end of summer, I will be declared by Fall. Since I am interested in AI I will try to get into CS188 but I need a backup... other classes are 61C, music 26AC and CS 195 so far(these can be changed around my upper-divs). I could try for 170 but due to its reputation I am scared of taking it as my first upper-div...I know this isn't a lot of info but any cool/fun upper division CS courses that are worth trying to get into? There are so many options to choose from.
